      "content": "Feeling short of breath with minimal activity is a sign your current routine is insufficient, not just \"getting older.\" Don't just rely on a single puff; you need a proper medical re-evaluation, which means you should definitely see a doctor. Tell them about the reduced effectiveness of your inhaler, and they can adjust your treatment plan with the correct, stronger medication.",
      "source": "target",
